{"updated_at": "2011-08-04T20:21:38Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2011-08-04T20:21:38Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1730371", "id": 1730371, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2424", "issue_id": 2424, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/repos", "type": "Organization", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mochaleaf", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "240b3c90db0dbb2b3121b2f9c3cb40b0", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/240b3c90db0dbb2b3121b2f9c3cb40b0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fab9e21de1c10cb71869e66fcb7a028a8.png", "id": 863132, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/events{/privacy}", "login": "Mochaleaf", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mochaleaf/followers"}, "body": "Ah, I'd say that the helpers .today and .yesterday shouldn't be appended onto the Date class then.. It's sort of strange behavior to have Date.today and Date.yesterday match one another.  It's also strange to have Date.today and Date.tomorrow be two days away from one another.\r\n\r\nIf Date.today shouldn't be used in a rails app, maybe we call the normal behavior and issue a warning saying to use Date.current?", "_id": {"$oid": "52384396bd3543c151010c56"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2424#issuecomment-1730371"}
